[[File:GEOSS Vače - panoramio.jpg|thumb|241px|Monument marking the Geometric Centre of Slovenia]]
{{Location map|Slovenia|label=|lat=46.12|long=14.82|position=left|caption=Geometric Centre of Slovenia}}
The '''Geometric Centre of Slovenia''' ({{lang-sl|Geometrično središče Slovenije}}, GEOSS) is the [[centroid|geometric centre]] of [[Slovenia|the country]]. Its [[Geographic coordinate system|geographic coordinates]] are  {{coord|46|07|11.8|N|14|48|55.2|E|type:landmark_region:SL|display=inline,title|}} and its elevation is 644.842 m.<ref>Inscription on the GEOSS monument.</ref> It lies in the hamlet of [[Slivna|Spodnja Slivna]] near [[Vače]] in the [[Municipality of Litija]]. Since 4 July 1982,<ref name="Drustvo">Društvo za razvoj in varovanje Geossa. ''GEOSS''. Information sign posted in Slivna.</ref> it has been marked with a memorial stone designed by the architect [[Marjan Božič]]. A plaque reading ''Živimo in gospodarimo na svoji zemlji'' ('We live and prosper upon our land') was added on 14 September 1989.<ref name="Drustvo"/> In 2003, Slovenia adopted an act on GEOSS.

