'''JOIDES Basin''' is a northeast trending undersea basin of the central [[Ross Dependency|Ross]] [[continental shelf]]. It was named for the "[[Joint Oceanographic Institutes Deep Earth Sampling]]" project, the name being approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1988.<ref name=gnis/>

