{{Infobox protected area | name = Kinmen National Park | iucn_category = II | photo = Kinmen National Park 20140830.JPG | photo_caption = | location = [[Kinmen|Kinmen County]], [[Republic of China]] | nearest_city = | map_image = KINMEN-National-Park.png | map_caption = Kinmen National Park area in Kinmen County | coordinates = {{Coord|24|26|52|N|118|21|52|E|display=inline,title}} | area_km2 = 35.29 | established = 18 October 1995 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }} The '''Kinmen National Park''' ({{zh|c=金門國家公園|p=Jīnmén Guójiā Gōngyuán}}) is a [[national park]] on the islands of [[Kinmen|Greater Kinmen]] and [[Lesser Kinmen]], administratively part of [[Kinmen County]], [[Republic of China]]. Kinmen National Park includes five areas, which are Taiwu Mountain, [[Battle of Kuningtou|Kuningtou]], Gugang, Mashan Hill and [[Lesser Kinmen|Lieyu]]. The park covers an area of 35.29&nbsp;km² or around a quarter of Kinmen County area.<ref name="MOI">{{cite web |url=http://np.cpami.gov.tw/chinese/filesys/statistics/103/253_b9fa691587eff16841128a4cea0c8276.pdf |script-title=zh:各國家公園基本資料表 |publisher=Construction and Planning Agency, Ministry of the Interior, R.O.C.(Taiwan) |format=PDF |language=Chinese |date=June 6, 2014 |accessdate=October 23, 2014 }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name="taiwantoday.tw">http://taiwantoday.tw/ct.asp?xItem=159132&ctNode=430</ref>
==History== The park was established in 1995.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kmnp.gov.tw/en/KinmenHistory.aspx|title=About The Park - Kinmen National Park|work=kmnp.gov.tw}}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
==Ecology== Due to its subtropical climate in its surrounding and low human population, the park becomes the place for migratory birds during autumn until spring. There has been 319 species of bird have been sighted in the area.<ref name="taiwantoday.tw"/>
==Types== * Scenic area * Historical preservation area * Recreational area * General restricted area
