See Mangerud et al. (2004)<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mangerud|first1=J.|last2=Jakobsson|first2=M.|last3=Alexanderson|first3=H.|last4=Astakhov|first4=V.|last5=Clarke|first5=G. K. C.|last6=Henriksen|first6=M.|last7=Hjort|first7=C.|last8=Krinner|first8=G.|last9=Lunkka|first9=J.-P.|last10=Möller|first10=P.|last11=Murray|first11=A.|last12=Nikolskaya|first12=O.|last13=Saarnisto|first13=M.|last14=Svendsen|first14=J. I.|title=Ice-dammed lakes and rerouting of the drainage of northern Eurasia during the Last Glaciation|journal=Quaternary Science Reviews|date=2004|volume=23|issue=11-13|pages=1313–1332|doi=10.1016/j.quascirev.2003.12.009}}</ref> for diagrams and descriptions of the lake as well as postulated drainage patterns.
